abstract: The sixth debate, hosted by PBS NewsHour and Politico, will be held at U.C.L.A. on Dec. 19.
snippet: The sixth debate, hosted by PBS NewsHour and Politico, will be held at U.C.L.A. on Dec. 19.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic National Committee announced on Friday that the sixth Democratic primary debate would be held in December at the University of California, Los Angeles, while ratcheting up the polling and donor criteria for candidates to qualify for a coveted spot onstage.

headline_main: California, Tulsi Gabbard, Betsy DeVos: Your Friday Briefing

abstract: Blackjewel went bankrupt in July and about 1,100 workers in central Appalachia lost several weeks of pay. In protest, coal miners blocked a train full of coal for months.
snippet: Blackjewel went bankrupt in July and about 1,100 workers in central Appalachia lost several weeks of pay. In protest, coal miners blocked a train full of coal for months.
lead_paragraph: For two months this summer, out-of-work miners blocked a train full of coal from shipping out of an eastern Kentucky mine, demanding weeks of unpaid wages after their employer, Blackjewel, suddenly went bankrupt.

headline_main: Blackjewel Coal Miners to Get Millions in Back Pay After Train Blockade

abstract: After ending the third quarter with less cash than four rivals, Joe Biden’s campaign reversed course to stop discouraging supporters from forming a super PAC to help him in the Democratic primary.
snippet: After ending the third quarter with less cash than four rivals, Joe Biden’s campaign reversed course to stop discouraging supporters from forming a super PAC to help him in the Democratic primary.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s campaign effectively dropped its longstanding opposition to receiving the assistance of super PACs on Thursday, opening the door for wealthy supporters to spend unlimited amounts of money to try and lift him in the Democratic primary.

headline_main: Biden Campaign Drops Opposition to Super PAC Support
headline_print_headline: With Less Cash Than Rivals, Biden Campaign Drops Its Opposition to Super PACs

abstract: Surveys released this week show varying, and sometimes conflicting, races unfolding nationally and in early primary states.
snippet: Surveys released this week show varying, and sometimes conflicting, races unfolding nationally and in early primary states.
lead_paragraph: Just over three months before Iowans caucus for Democratic presidential candidates, four polls out this week present a muddled picture of a primary race that is unfolding in varying, and sometimes conflicting, ways nationally and in early-voting states.

abstract: School strikes have put teachers in the spotlight. But demands for more counselors, nurses and psychologists are growing.
snippet: School strikes have put teachers in the spotlight. But demands for more counselors, nurses and psychologists are growing.
lead_paragraph: In a typical week, Adrienne Vaccarezza-Isla, a school counselor in Chicago, might help a dozen eighth graders apply to high schools across the city. Or try to convince a mother that her daughter, who had seen her get shot years earlier, should join a group for students dealing with trauma. Or work with sixth and seventh graders on time management.

abstract: Trump’s foreign policy disasters should lead liberals to rediscover the perils of geopolitical retreat.
snippet: Trump’s foreign policy disasters should lead liberals to rediscover the perils of geopolitical retreat.
lead_paragraph: Donald Trump’s abrupt withdrawal of U.S. forces from Syria has drawn widespread scorn from Republicans and Democrats alike, and with good reason: The U.S. has betrayed an ally and ceded influence to a gallery of rogues — Bashar al-Assad, Recep Tayyip Erdogan, Vladimir Putin and Qassim Suleimani, to name a few — in exchange for a hollow talking point about ending endless wars.
